â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“„ WebsiteTrackingPage.tsx
â”‚   â”‚   Purpose: Allows users to get their website tracking pixel script and verify its installation.
â”‚   â”‚   Details:
â”‚   â”‚     - Uses the shared `@/components/Navbar`. Jungle-themed styling.
â”‚   â”‚     - Fetches the authenticated user's `email_setup_id` from the `email_setups` table.
â”‚   â”‚     - Dynamically generates a JavaScript pixel script that includes:
â”‚   â”‚       - The user's unique `email_setup_id`.
â”‚   â”‚       - The URL for the `ingest-tracking-event` Supabase function.
â”‚   â”‚       - Logic to automatically send an `emailore_pixel_loaded` event when the script loads on the user's website.
â”‚   â”‚       - Exposes a `window.emailore.track(eventName, eventData)` function for custom event tracking.
â”‚   â”‚     - Displays the generated pixel script in a `<pre>` tag with a "Copy to Clipboard" button.
â”‚   â”‚     - Provides clear instructions on how and where to install the pixel script on their website (e.g., in the `<head>` tag).
â”‚   â”‚     - Features a "Test Pixel Installation" button.
â”‚   â”‚       - When clicked, this button calls the `test-pixel-status` Supabase Edge Function, passing the `email_setup_id`.
â”‚   â”‚       - The `test-pixel-status` function checks the `tracked_events` table for a recent (`<10 minutes`) `emailore_pixel_loaded` event associated with the `email_setup_id`.
â”‚   â”‚     - Displays feedback to the user based on the test result (loading state, success message with checkmark, or failure message with warning triangle and details).
â”‚   â”‚     - Includes "Previous" navigation to `/dns-confirmation`.
â”‚   â”‚     - The "Next" button reads "Continue to Plan Selection" and navigates to `/subscription-plan` (using `FORM_FLOW_ORDER`).
â”‚   â”‚   Usage: Step in the multi-step onboarding flow, after `/dns-confirmation` and before `/subscription-plan`. Provides the means for users to implement website activity tracking for Emailore.
